 The Multris font is slightly based on \TeX's {\tt cmr} fonts.


WHAT IS THIS?

 This is `Multris', a Tetris-clone.  This is a pre-release version, but not
 just a pre-release version.  It has many options and looks nice. You don't
 have to read these docs to be able to play it.


CONTROL

		|Joystick		Keyboard		Keypad
 ---------------+-----------------------------------------------------
 Left		|Left			J			4  <
 Right		|Right			L			6  >
 Down		|Down						2  v
 Clockwise	|			I			8  ^
 C. Clockwise   |Button			K			5
 Drop		|			<Space>			0  Ins

 I didn't really spend much time on the joystick part, so it's rotten.


THIS IS THE *TH TETRIS-CLONE!

 It is indeed.  If you ask me, the perfect Tetris still does not exist. But
 this one comes close. In fact, the only thing the final version will lack,
 is good response to pressed keys.


WHAT CAN'T YOU DO?

 These  are the options you don't have in this version,  but will appear in
 the next version:
 o Save and load your configurations,  thus allowing you to design your own
   library of styles.
 o Assign your own keys to the available movements:  turn right, turn left,
   move right, move left, move down and drop.
 o Design your own block-styles (sprites used for the blocks) using an IFF-
   paint program like DPaint.
 o Optional music/sound/silence.
	
 These are the options you don't have  in  this  version  and  might  never
 appear in any future release:
 o Design your own block-sets.
 o Levels which allready have blocks in it (like the Arcade version).
 o See the next block.


