PROGRAMMERS

 If you're planning to make Tetris, please read the programmers-guide; it's
 almost impossible to write a good Tetris if you haven't given it plenty of
 thought.   This was my third version  (my first was on a CBM 64)  and it's
 finally pretty OK.


OTHER TETRIS CLONES

 These are some other Tetris clones:
 T-Triz (2.0) Great music and BIG blocks.  Unfortunately,  you tend to keep
	      your eyes on the lower left corner of the screen.   Are you a
	      Maestro?
 Tetron       Many options, especially in future versions. It's a bit slow,
	      but the arcade-type levels are real tough.
 Colors       Looks nice, plays nice and has poor sounds. It isn't really a
	      Tetris, it's a combination of Tetris and Othello.
 Zetris       Run's in a window on your Workbench screen.  Nothing special.
 Hextris      Tetris with six-sides blocks.   Takes a while to get used to,
	      but it's fun to play.
 Intereferon  A bit like Colors.  Looks nice,  sounds nice, plays nice, but
	      you won't get hooked to it.
 Tettrix      Awfull  control and bad sounds.   It does show the next three
	      blocks, though.
 Sizetris     Well, it might have been nice if it worked properly.


FUN

 Have fun with Multris!
